<figureCitation box="[926,985,545,567]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,196,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,196,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Heads and pronota of Peripus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 5. Peripus brunkei Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 6. Peripus didontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 7. Peripus madrededios Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 8. Peripus monodontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354780/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), antennomeres 8–10 clearly longer than wide; aedeagus as 
<figureCitation box="[346,1345,575,597]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–26" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1935,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,1185,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,1178,1896]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–26. Aedeagus of P. didontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 24. Dorsal view. 25. Lateral view. 26. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354788/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
Figs. 24–26........................................................................ 
<taxonomicName box="[1330,1345,576,597]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Peripus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="didontus">
<emphasis box="[1330,1345,576,597]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">P</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</figureCitation>
. didontus
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,545,832]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
<keyLead pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
- Pronotum punctation not as dense (
<figureCitation box="[566,683,604,626]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,196,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,196,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Heads and pronota of Peripus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 5. Peripus brunkei Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 6. Peripus didontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 7. Peripus madrededios Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 8. Peripus monodontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354780/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Figs. 5, 7–8</figureCitation>
), punctures not contiguous; antennomeres 8–10 subquadrate to slightly longer than wide........................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,545,832]" box="[151,1436,663,685]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,663,685]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
2. Median lobe with two subapical teeth; paramere pointed apically (
<figureCitation box="[862,931,663,685]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,936,961]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,181,905]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,916]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 27–29. Aedeagus of P. madrededios Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 27. Dorsal view. 28. Lateral view. 29. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354792/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
