<emphasis box="[1290,1436,663,685]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">P. madrededios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,545,832]" box="[151,1436,692,714]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,692,714]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
- Median lobe with one subapical tooth; paramere rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[870,950,692,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1082,1107]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,344,1040]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,344,1051]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Aedeagus of P. brunkei Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 21. Dorsal view. 22. Lateral view. 23. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354786/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Figs. 23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[960,985,692,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–32" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1762,1787]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1019,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,1019,1743]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30–32. Aedeagus of P. monodontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 30. Dorsal view. 31. Lateral view. 32. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">32</figureCitation>
)................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,545,832]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
<keyLead pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
3 Paramere converging to apex (
<figureCitation box="[520,592,721,744]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1082,1107]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,344,1040]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,344,1051]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Aedeagus of P. brunkei Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 21. Dorsal view. 22. Lateral view. 23. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354786/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
); paramere shorter than median lobe (
<figureCitation box="[957,1075,721,744]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1082,1107]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,344,1040]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,344,1051]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Aedeagus of P. brunkei Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 21. Dorsal view. 22. Lateral view. 23. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354786/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Figs. 21–22</figureCitation>
); pronotum punctation with 1–2 rows of scattered punctures (besides punctures on the midline; 
<figureCitation box="[778,834,751,773]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,196,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,196,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Heads and pronota of Peripus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 5. Peripus brunkei Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 6. Peripus didontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 7. Peripus madrededios Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 8. Peripus monodontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354780/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
)......................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1339,1436,751,773]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Peripus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunkei">
<emphasis box="[1339,1436,751,773]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">P. brunkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,545,832]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
<keyLead pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
- Paramere slightly expanding to apex (
<figureCitation box="[590,662,780,802]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–32" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1762,1787]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1019,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,1019,1743]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30–32. Aedeagus of P. monodontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 30. Dorsal view. 31. Lateral view. 32. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
); paramere slightly longer than median lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1218,780,802]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–32" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1762,1787]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1019,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,1019,1743]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30–32. Aedeagus of P. monodontus Chatzimanolis &amp; Hightower. 30. Dorsal view. 31. Lateral view. 32. Detail of paramere, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3354794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Figs. 30–31</figureCitation>
